values:
Not much, just a quick post to say I excitingly met a livejournaler in the flesh last night.  Way cool :) and hello to ozdeadmeat if you're out there.

Trying to get ahold of the boy, methinks he bes sick.  And that's all :)

Hope everyone else is well.

It'd be a shame if I had a serious problem to talk about.

I made an appointment last week with a counsellor - stupid idea I know, but I felt like talking - anyway it was for 1:30 today.  At 12:20 I get a voicemail:

'Hi Alex, we've had to cancel your appointment for today. If you decide to make another one please call back.'

Then one of them actually gets a hold of me and says the same thing.
So am I going to make a new appointment?  No, of course not.  It was stupid of me to want to talk about something I was upset about, and stupid to decide to go to a proper counseelor after all this time of not doing it.
And besides which, why go to a place that so obviously doesn't have much concern or respect for clients?

Meh, I'll learn from my mistakes.

Other than that all is good.  Hope you're all going good to :)

Hungover as heck after the raddness last night at Cell Block 69.
*sigh* much love for Corey Axelrod...

Feel like an almost dead person today though, and happy people keep calling for help.  Why isn't everyone on leave already darn it...

:)

Merry [insert celebration you celebrate here] to everyone.  Hope it's a fun one and hope you all have fantasicly, drunkenly , merrily, funnly holidays and New Years :D

Am very, very bored, but my cursor is a mermaid, so that's cool.
Northern territory in 3 and a bit weeks, which means seein Mum, Shana, Uluru and my tattooist :)  Yay!  New tattoo for Alex!
Am trying to think of something nice and vegetarian for dinner tonight, am thinking home made herby potato chips and salad...  Damn living with one vegetarian and dating another!
The dating one is coming over tonight, the living with one is going out for dinner...
Am sleepy and just had the first and only bad nashi of my life.  I don't want that experience again.
Am playing around with Facebook and on my lunch break because it's too damn cold outside.  It was so warm when I left the house this morning too.  Stoopid weather!

01. What is essential for your happiness?
Breathing balls and boys!  Can't live without boys.  That or a healthy supply of St Johns Wart in all it's various forms and no lactose.

02. What clothes are you wearing at the moment?
Black long sleeve top, White singlet top, red and black belt, grey hat, jeans, stockings and my orange Doc Martens.  Oh, and underwears, several pairs :P

03. What games did you recently play?
Lego Indiana Jones, Portal, Hexic, and various Xbox arcade games.  Also Cheat and 500 (card games)

04. What is your favorite scent?
The blood of my fallen enemies...  with a hint of mint, from real mint leaves.

05. What books are you reading at the moment?
Re-reading the Obernewtyn Chronicles - up to book four, Hitchhikers Guide, An Agatha and a Terry Pratchett and some other bits and pieces.

06. What do you drink the most?
Water.  I drink so much water these days.  and anything containing alcohol.

07. Do you trust easily?
Way too easily.  I like people when they're high up on pedestals as well.

08. Who was your first big crush?
Dustin Hoffman as Hook, then Tim Curry... Also Brian Hastings from school.  I loved him :)

09. What did you want to be when you grew up?
First woman on the moon.

10. Do you have a good body image?
If you squint and are wearing beer goggles...  Also, when I'm in a moo-moo, no one looks as good  in a moo-moo as me :P

11. Do you have a crush?
*giggle*  Yes'm.

12. What websites do you visit daily?
These days, the work ones, LiveJournal, Google, Sydney Morning Herald, The Australian.

13. Random pet peeve?
People whose voices go up at the end of sentences...  actually, that's just funny.  I'm hard to annoy.

14. What's your favorite word?
Schadenfreude.

15. What's the last song that got stuck in your head?
You can't always get what you want - The Rolling Stones.

16. What's your favorite item of clothing?
My hat.

17. What's better: to give or to receive?
Receive, because then people have to be nice to you and talk about how great you are :P

18. What turns you on in your preferred gender(s)?
Buttons, toggles, switches.

19. Is there anything you want really badly right now?
Moneies - I want to go to Hotel Atlantis in Dubai.

20. What should you be doing right now?
Working.

21. What’s the meaning behind your LJ username/name/nicknames you go by?
I had a hulahoop and I set up my livejournal account.  Very exciting.

22. What are some things that you are proud to have accomplished recently? Go ahead and brag!
I bought the boxed Split Enz set... that was pretty cool.  Also three years, pretty nifty...

First of all today marks 1096 days with the Glitter Fairy. It would have looked cooler as 1095 days, damn leap years.
Second of all the sister is having radness time in the homeland (and by that I mean England where we all come from).
Third of all the mother is still in the Northern Territory and lovin' it, am going to visit her soon.
Fourth of all the father just spent the weekend in Melbourne and is going to bank my tax return for me this week.
Fifth of all the baby brother is actually graduating college this year. Is a little weird.
Sixth of all I hate the weather, can't it just decide if it want to be cold or hot? I keep wearing dodgy clothes to work under jumpers and having to take jumpers off and look dodgy, or die of heat exhaustion...
Seventh of all, poor Rob Guest. The world totall has to stop killing the favourits - Pavarotti - my favourite musician, Arthur C. Clarke - my favourite scientist.author/invetor/all-round-good-guy, George Carlin - my favourite American stand up comedian and dodgy priest, Sir Edmund Hillary - my favourite mountain climber (because I know of so many) and the list keeps going and now Rob Guest - my favourite musical star. So just to make it clear, from now on ayone you've ever heard me adore I now hate, just to keep them safe...
Eighth of all how's everyone doing these days? I haven't seen/heard from so many of you guys in so long. Let me know what's the happie-hap!
Ninth of all Glitter Fairy is looking at flying away to Melbourne very soon with plans for me to follow next year posibli...
Tenth of all I can't seem to unbold or unitalics this writing.  Have learnt my lesson, will never play with fots again...

Bub bye!

Blarrrgh!

Alex is sleepy.
Alex is working at DEEWR which is nice.
Alex is now living in Higgins which is also nice.
Alex misses people at Borders though.
Alex is still seeing the Glitter Fairy - almost 3 years.
Alex needs a Jan to hang around while she's typing in third person.
Alex wishes that the Brady Bunch will come back onto TV.
Alex might update more often in the future now that she's on the inter-web everyday.
Alex hopes you've all been well.
Alex is going now.

bub bye :)

Just a random post, I found an internet and computer that works, in retalliation to the abuse I got today from whom I will continue calling my namesakee's parents :P
This is me, I resigned from my job today...
Huzzah!

50% GeekMingle2.com - Free Online Dating Oh dear... So I saw an odd interview today when watching a little of the ANZAC stuff. This guy was oulling randoms out asking questions about the day, if they lost anyone etc, and also, how does your sub-culture/demographic celebrate ANZAC day. He as pulling different people out by the way they looked, derro guy, man in a suit etc then asked a girl in black pants and a long black coat, but not at all gothy, near me so I could hear her answers. When asked how her sub-culture/demographic celebrated ANZAC day she looked down and smiled saying, you mean goth? He agreed so she said that her and her friends cut themselves to symbolise the blood of the men who died, drank the blood to symbolise mother earth taking back her sons then ate Turkish fr dinner/ He was stumped working out if she was serious or not and all he could say was, 'do you do thisevery year?' It was brilliant :D The glitter fairy's birthday is this Sunday, still ain't got all his pressie together. Damn those boyfriend types! Mickey's birthday was last weekend, it was funky in all different ways, if only I could remember it all. I put cut up wigs all through my hair, am going to get a fringe cut, and am trangely tempted to dye it pinkish purple and yellow :P Not much else. Still working, nothing much is happening there, except now we have awesome regular lunatic customers, all three of which I've been stuck with whenever they come, but they're fun and minus the fustration it's worth it. Also, Jeremy Ions look-a-like came to work today. He was very short, but so sexy anyway :D All us gals made sure we saw him... *swoon* Blarh... May just run away now... Oh, my hotmail account is working again, so is all good to be emailed too! Woot!

So, obviously I've disappeared :)

As most of you know Mickey, Sam and I moved out, living the good life, with kittens!  And therefore I am quite without the internet, ergo no emailing.

Am still working at Borders, and I really like it there :)  still going out with the glitter fairy, I like it there too.  Still have no idea what to actually do with my life.  Clearing out my inbox seems to be what I'll be doing forever.

One of my old teachers is Dan's principal and asked Mum and Dad about me and told them what a great student I was :) made me happy.

My kitten is the cutest thing in the world!

Not really a lot to say.  Rose is back in the country, can't wait to see her :D

Love to all!

I'm now 21, Yay!  So old.
Am trying to quit smoking, my room is very clean now.  I want one, trying not to think about how much I'd love one.  *sigh*
Am sick, which aids the quitting smoking thing as I'm at home all day, I don't like to smoke in front of parents, plus I get to sleep all day.
I'm not doing well so far, but at last I've cut it down heaps and have no more left to smoke.

Smoke, smoke, smoke.

Anyway. My birthday was rad, I got presents and affection.  Affection is rad!  I got a digital camera so I can now bombard livejournal with photo's of me, looking rad. Oh yeah!  Plus pgoto's in general.  Got a Fairy floss maker which will be broken in on saturday night.  Man, I want fairy floss.

Have been really slack lately.

Borders is rad, people are very nice and sending me get better messages.  The boys out back got me a birthday cake and Borders gave me a sex kitten reindeer toy.  Plus, you know, everyone there is really nice and friendly in general.

Am going to run away now before I get told off for typing too loud.

Yay! People (or more person) have managed to amuse me once more with their silliness. Rose and I were at her house last night drink wine and watching the interview with Terri Irwin by Ray Martin. It was great, she would get really teary and sob and Ray would lean over, pat her knee and ask the next question. Watching it prompted me to start looking around for Steve Irwin jokes, I've been disappointed by the amount I haven't been hearing. there's so few, and the people who do put them up get 'yelled' at for being so insensitive. If anyone has any can they please write them in a comment to me?

Hey-a...

Just a small update to say that we raised $687.45 on saturday night for Spina Bifida and Hydrocephalus.  Dad's going to take the total up to $700, I believe Mum suggested that he do it.  I had an awesome night, I hope everyone who went did too.

I spent sunday with Nick, James and Craig alternately driving Nick insane with my awesomely awful Pikmin skills, and being driven insane by Craig and James and their 'beautiful music'.
Craig and I played Gamecube late into the night last night, trying to remember how to unlock the secret characters in Smashbrothers (?) Smashsomething.  We unlocked Jigglypuff.  No one tell us how to get the others, I want to work it out (or beg Daniel when I get too frustrated with it).

The wedding was on saturday afternoon, and it was beautiful.  Trish looked gorgeous and Adam was very handsome. Adam's parents were very sweet; his Dad asking if he could keep both when told that Mickey would be handing him the microphone after singing and his Mum after the ceremony thanking us for our 'beautiful music'.  There were butterflies that didn't want to leave the box in a hurry, Craig, Mickey and I played well, the binding was really nice, hopefully Adam was suitably surprised by Songbird.

So all in all a good week in the land of Alex.  (Including getting the job.  Yay!)

Very sleepy now, might go back to bed before cycling to Ginninderra Gardens to give the written resignation.

The orangey one is Moby Dick (named by Mum) and the black one is Kitty (named by Mickey). I wanted to call them Alex and Craig but he wouldn't allow it. He also won't accept that he's now a daddy of my fishies :( Poor Daddy-less fishies... We think the orangey one might be pregnant, poor bastard baby fishies the Moby Dick might have... In other news, going to Lot 32 later to be amazed by John and Sam's leet dj-ing skills. Waiting for the football to finish before we go. Go Broncos (the fishies go for the Broncos at the moment as well) And more other news COME TO SPINA BIFIDA CHARITY TOMORROW NIGHT!!! If you love me you will :)

Mickey bought me fishies!

The black one is called Kitty and the orange one is called Moby Dick (Moby for short)

Photo's coming soon!

I got a job at Borders :)  Very happy.  There's an induction thingy on the 14th October, wow, just realised my last name is similar to october, Proctor - October...  Kinda but not really.
Very happy :)

The Seven Sins
 
WRATH.

1. Who did you last get angry with? I don't know...
2. What is your weapon of choice? A love ray

4. How about of the same sex? Sure, why not, have done in the past.
5. Who was the last person who got really angry with you? Probably my parents
6. What is your pet peeve? Being broke
7. Do you keep grudges, or can you let them go easily? Depends what the grudge is about.

 SLOTH.

1. What is one thing you're supposed to do daily that you haven't? Brush my teeth before bed (Still have time :))
2. What is the latest you've ever woken up? Something p.m.
4. What is the last lame excuse you made?  I'd rather be a hooker.

6. When was the last time you got in a good workout? I walked forever today.
7. How many times did you hit the snooze button on your alarm clock today? Once.

GLUTTONY.

1. What is your overpriced yuppie beverage of choice? Carlton?  I have no idea.
2. Meat eaters: white meat or dark meat? Either or.
3. What is the greatest amount of alcohol you've had in one sitting/outing/event?No idea, a hell of a lot.
4. Have you ever used a professional diet company? Nope, but it's been tempting...

6. Do you prefer sweets, salty foods, or spicy? Everything!
7. Have you ever looked at a small house pet or child and thought "lunch"? Yes >:D

 LUST.

1. How many people have you seen naked (not counting movies/family): Six or seven.
2. How many people have seen YOU naked (not counting physicians/family): Three or four.

4. Have you "done it"?  Many times baby.  Yeah, a couple of times.

GREED.

1. How many credit cards do you own? None, but I'm thinking of getting one.
2. What's your guilty pleasure store? Music shops of any callibre.
3. Would you rather be rich, or famous? Either or.
4. Would you accept a boring job if it meant you would make mega bucks? Possibly. How boring?
5. Have you ever stolen anything? A matchbox car for Daniel when Mickey and I were young.
6. How many MP3s are on your hard drive? No idea.

PRIDE.

1. What's one thing you have done that you're most proud of? Not sure I've done anything I'm proud of...  I'll think about that for a bit.
2. Whats one thing you have done that your parents are most proud of?  Telling off people in a disabled space, organising this charity thingy.
3. What things would you like to accomplish in your life? No idea, at least one thing would be good.
4. Do you get annoyed by coming in second place? Nope.
5. Have you ever entered a contest of skill, knowing you were of much higher skill than all the other competitors? I don't think so, I might have done though...
6. Have you ever cheated on something to get a higher score?  Yup.

ENVY.

1. What item (or person) of your friends would you most want to have for your own? Looks I suppose, but I'm over all that now a days.
2. Who would you want to go on "Trading Spaces" with? I don't know what that is.
3. If you could be anyone else in the world, who would you be? Someone not lactose intolerant so that when I had milk I wouldn't be sad, also someone who doesn't put on weight by looking at food.  actually I wouldn't switch with anyone.
4. Have you ever been cheated on? Yes.
5. Have you ever wished you had a physical feature different from your own? In the past I have, but similar to question 1, I'm over that now.
6. What inborn trait do you see in others that you wish you had for yourself? I don't know...
7. Do you wish you'd come up with this survey? Nope.

So, I'm browsing through the net reading all I can on Scientology, trying to find the Wall of fire stuff.

I've found heaps of stuff about Lisa McPherson (she's one of their followers who died while in their care) and various other followers who passed on.  Several reports and stories from people who have left, or quit or been thrown out or whatever, many, many things about Xenu (which you learn about at OT3) but still nothing about OT8 and the Wall of Fire and stuff that can cause you to die if you read it unprepared.  *sigh*  Will continue looking though.

I love that unprepared people who read OT3 (the Xenu story)  could catch pneumonia and die...

Tee hee!  They talk to animals and trees :)  Cute!  And then I find this....

"For those of you whose Christian toes I may have stepped on, let me take the opportunity to disabuse you of some lovely myths. For instance, the historic Jesus was not nearly the sainted figure has been made out to be. In addition to being a lover of young boys and men, he was given to uncontrollable bursts of temper and hatred that belied the general message of love, understanding and other typical Marcab PR."


Oh my God!!!!!!!!  I'm offended, incredibly offended.  Apparently Marcab is an invader force or something.

Hmm, the Xenu thing seems to be it, I can't find any other secrets at all online.  How depressing.

Well, having read all I can about the Wall of Fire and what not, I suppose we'll see if I get pneumonia.  I'm going to give it two weeks before I decide that I shan't get pneumonia.  If I get pneumonia in that time I'll sell all my possessions and give all my money to Scientology.

So, I woke up an hour ago.  I worked a double overnight, so I was at work from 3ish yesterday to 7:15 this morning.  Very fecked now.

On the other hand...

SPLIT ENZ!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  TOMORROW!!!!!!!!!!!!

Very muchly looking forward to it.

Am going to go die now.
